                    <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                            <i class="ri-global-line text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">
                                Top 10 Online Sources for Building Materials in the US
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
                                These days, it seems like everyone buys things online, and this trend extends to online sources for building materials in the US. Major suppliers include Home Depot, Lowe's, Menards, and specialized sites like BuildDirect, Material Bank, and 84 Lumber. Online purchasing offers convenience, competitive pricing, and access to specialty products not available locally.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="openModal(8)" class="inline-flex items-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 font-medium hover:text-primary-800 dark:hover:text-primary-300 text-sm cursor-pointer">
                        View Sources <i class="ri-arrow-right-line ml-2"></i>
                    </button>
                </div>

                <!-- Save Money -->
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                    <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-yellow-100 dark:bg-yellow-900 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                            <i class="ri-money-dollar-circle-line text-yellow-600 dark:text-yellow-400 text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">
                                How to Save Money on Construction Materials?
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
                                Construction materials take up a significant part of the construction cost. Higher the cost of construction materials, higher will be the building cost. Strategies to save include bulk purchasing, buying during off-season, using standard sizes, comparing multiple suppliers, considering recycled materials, and establishing long-term relationships with vendors for better pricing.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="openModal(9)" class="inline-flex items-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 font-medium hover:text-primary-800 dark:hover:text-primary-300 text-sm cursor-pointer">
                        Save Money <i class="ri-arrow-right-line ml-2"></i>
                    </button>
                </div>

                <!-- Buy Online -->
                <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
                    <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
                            <i class="ri-shopping-bag-line text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400 text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-2">
                                How to Buy Construction Materials Online
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
                                Ordering construction materials can be an intimidating process, especially if you're new to the construction industry. Start by researching reputable suppliers, comparing prices, reading reviews, and understanding shipping costs and return policies. Create detailed material lists with exact specifications to ensure you receive correct items, and consider ordering samples when possible.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="openModal(10)" class="inline-flex items-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 font-medium hover:text-primary-800 dark:hover:text-primary-300 text-sm cursor-pointer">
                        Buy Guide <i class="ri-arrow-right-line ml-2"></i>
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Additional Articles -->
        <div class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-6 pb-3 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                More Material Guides
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <!-- Modified Bitumen -->
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">What is Modified Bitumen Roofing and Why Do Flat Roofs Love It?</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">Modified bitumen roofing is a key component in the construction of commercial properties. It combines asphalt with polymer modifiers for enhanced flexibility and durability, making it ideal for low-slope roofs. Installation can be done by torch-application, cold adhesive, or self-adhering methods.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="openModal(11)" class="mt-2 md:mt-0 md:ml-4 px-4 py-2 bg-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 dark:hover:bg-primary-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer">
                        Read Article
                    </button>
                </div>

                <!-- ADU Cost -->
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">How Much Does it Cost to Build an Accessory Dwelling Unit?</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">Wondering how much it costs to build an ADU? On average, building an Accessory Dwelling Unit costs between $100,000 and $300,000 depending on size, location, and finishes. Factors affecting cost include foundation type, utilities connections, kitchen and bathroom installations, and local permitting fees.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="openModal(12)" class="mt-2 md:mt-0 md:ml-4 px-4 py-2 bg-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 dark:hover:bg-primary-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer">
                        Read Article
                    </button>
                </div>

                <!-- Concrete Setting -->
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">How Long Does It Take for Concrete to Set?</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">Concrete is one of the most widely used materials in construction due to its strength and durability. Initial setting time typically takes 24-48 hours, but concrete reaches about 70% of its full strength within 7 days and achieves full cure after 28 days. Factors affecting curing include temperature, humidity, and concrete mix design.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="openModal(13)" class="mt-2 md:mt-0 md:ml-4 px-4 py-2 bg-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 dark:hover:bg-primary-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer">
                        Read Article
                    </button>
                </div>

                <!-- Cutting and Filling -->
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center justify-between bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-750 transition-colors">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1">Cutting and Filling in Construction Earthwork – Explained Clearly</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">Cutting and filling are essential techniques in earthwork: moving and shaping soil and rock to prepare land for construction. Cut refers to removing material from high areas, while fill adds material to low areas to achieve desired grades. Proper calculations ensure balanced earthwork minimizing material import/export costs.</p>
                    </div>
                    <button onclick="openModal(14)" class="mt-2 md:mt-0 md:ml-4 px-4 py-2 bg-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 dark:hover:bg-primary-600 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap cursor-pointer">
                        Read Article
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Material Comparison Table -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-6">Common Materials Comparison</h3>
